This app is still excellent for 531 but for almost a year now I have used it to log Juggernaut program from Chad Wesley Smith. I run the program with the 'going heavy' addendum and undulating waves. So 10/5/8/3. Juggernaut is similar in structure to 531 but with more attention to volume and frequency. Due to Juggernaut structural similarity this app is perfect to use to track it. I can add sets and adjust weight easily and the maths for 1rm and 90% 1rm are still calculated by the app. Wave results are still logged and monthly progression is to view however it's only every 4 months that you really need to test you new 1rm. I find JM a superior program to 531 and am glad this app allows me to log with ease.

As an aside, Jim updated 5/3/1 (And also 'Beyond 5/3/1') with '5/3/1 Forever', which has some great material. Might be worth considering for future features.

replyContent:
Hi Kyle,
1.You can modify the OHP weights as follows.
On OHP day, select the stalled option from the workout menu. Enter a new TM (90%) of your 1RM. The app will recalculate and update weights for all upcoming OHP sessions.

2. If you just want to view the weights, select overview, cycle number and tap on a  cycle .This will show the main weights.
